ODE VI.

As the former Odes are addressed more to qualities of young men, this refers more especially to the vices of young women, and so Horace discharges the promise with whlch this series of Odes begins. Tho state of female mor- als at the time Horace wrote was probably not so bad as it became shortly afterwards, though his picture is dark enough. “
